{
  "texts": [
    "In order to better cope with the cold-start problem for new items and alleviate the temporal generalization problem of LLMs, a vector database is utilized to provide information for new items that the LLMs are unaware of in Chat-REC [225].",
    "When encountering new items, LLMs can utilize this database to access information about them based on the similarity between the user's request embedding and item embeddings in the database.",
    "User profiles can also help LLMs better understand the user's intent.",
    "RecLLM [226] employs a user profile module as a tool to deposit meaningful and enduring facts about users exposed during historical conversations in user memory and retrieve a single fact related to the current dialogue when necessary.Although some works have applied the concept of tool learning to personalization systems, there are still interesting and promising research topics that deserve exploration.",
    "1) Fine-tuning models for better tool use."
  ]
}